<subSubSection id="8DA9D805173BF8064FEFEA03BF1E9CEC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="host">
<paragraph id="8D732DBAE22D4177245541D421380A1F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Host plants.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AD7A783FBD113FE3D59A3BC9A2B99B25" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Recorded from two species of 
<taxonomicName id="1CB6B482576C7F3EE3F34EF6B4C9F260" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Dipterocarpaceae" genus="Dipterocarpus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dipterocarpus" order="Malvales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="320B8A73A36BDD31D57CB3DE90A8750A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Dipterocarpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="7BCF84EFF6746A20AA0F0FFA6D33D67E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Dipterocarpaceae" genus="Dipterocarpus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malvales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Dipterocarpaceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="110B05C51C45FE7D70F0C788A734C860" author="Maiti, PK" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Survey of India, Kolkata" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B253" refString="Maiti, PK, Saha, N, 2004. Fauna of India and the Adjacent Countries. Scolytidae: Coleoptera (Bark- and Ambrosia-beetles) (Vol. 1). Part-1. Introduction and Tribe Xyleborini. Zoological Survey of India, Kolkata" title="Fauna of India and the Adjacent Countries. Scolytidae: Coleoptera (Bark- and Ambrosia-beetles) (Vol. 1). Part- 1. Introduction and Tribe Xyleborini." year="2004">Maiti and Saha 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="867679BF51BA34D3B4809796511DC823" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="E58F788FE640B012B863012B34AECA37" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="093ED4EAFF6DFD5410FE56275D2D576F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species is transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="B6EA7C95DEC6735AE92D37F74AA9A774" authorityName="Hopkins" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Arixyleborus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Arixyleborus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="712426C36CBF94E28ADF76862A2289AE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Arixyleborus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="AC0264BFFA8F3267B0B36E0888402F22" authorityName="Lea" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Amasa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Amasa" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="65AD08BC377AB7314595B6AB9225F7F0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Amasa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species displays a superficial morphological resemblance to 
<taxonomicName id="4508DB3B6913163C44C7EF393E6CDAE7" authorityName="Lea" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Amasa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Amasa" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="80F71EFAC44B9EC43799353CBF97BAAA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Amasa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however it possesses the unique characteristics exhibited by 
<taxonomicName id="EB9DEBDE10CD4CA0EC493748D4DC0C40" authorityName="Hopkins" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Arixyleborus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Arixyleborus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1C1F6F8CE365D474BDB324C71EBB9B8E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Arixyleborus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
including protibiae slender, inflated and granulate on posterior faces, antennal club type 2, six striae present on the declivity, and pronotum from dorsal view elongated basic shape with rounded frontal margin (type 7).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
